## [§](https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls/latest/hyper_rustls/#hyper-rustls)hyper-rustls
A pure-Rust HTTPS connector for [hyper](https://hyper.rs), based on [Rustls](https://github.com/rustls/rustls).
### [§](https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls/latest/hyper_rustls/#example-client)Example client
```
use http::StatusCode;
use http_body_util::Empty;
use hyper::body::Bytes;
use hyper_util::client::legacy::Client;
use hyper_util::rt::TokioExecutor;
let mut rt = tokio::runtime::Runtime::new().unwrap();
let url = ("https://hyper.rs").parse().unwrap();
let https = hyper_rustls::HttpsConnectorBuilder::new()
  .with_native_roots()
  .expect("no native root CA certificates found")
  .https_only()
  .enable_http1()
  .build();
let client: Client<_, Empty<Bytes>> = Client::builder(TokioExecutor::new()).build(https);
let res = rt.block_on(client.get(url)).unwrap();
assert_eq!(res.status(), StatusCode::OK);
```

# hyper-rustls
This is an integration between the [Rustls TLS stack](https://github.com/rustls/rustls) and the [hyper HTTP library](https://github.com/hyperium/hyper).
[![Build Status](https://img.gs/czjpqfbdkz/full/https://github.com/rustls/hyper-rustls/actions/workflows/build.yml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/rustls/hyper-rustls/actions) [![Crate](https://img.shields.io/crates/v/hyper-rustls.svg)](https://crates.io/crates/hyper-rustls) [![Documentation](https://img.gs/czjpqfbdkz/full/https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls/badge.svg)](https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls)
# Release history
Release history can be found [on GitHub](https://github.com/rustls/hyper-rustls/releases).
# License
hyper-rustls is distributed under the following three licenses:
  * Apache License version 2.0.
  * MIT license.
  * ISC license.


These are included as LICENSE-APACHE, LICENSE-MIT and LICENSE-ISC respectively. You may use this software under the terms of any of these licenses, at your option.
## Running examples
### server
```
```cargo``` run`` --`example` server`
`
```

### client
```
```cargo``` run`` --`example` client ``"`https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls/latest/hyper_rustls/`"```
`
```

## Crate features
This crate exposes a number of features to add support for different portions of ``hyper-util``, ``rustls``, and other dependencies.
Feature flag | Enabled by default | Description  
---|---|---  
``aws-lc-rs`` | **yes** | Enables use of the [AWS-LC](https://docs.rs/aws-lc-rs) backend for [``rustls``](https://docs.rs/rustls)  
``http1`` | **yes** | Enables HTTP/1 support in [``hyper-util``](https://docs.rs/hyper-util)  
``http2`` | **no** | Enables HTTP/2 support in [``hyper-util``](https://docs.rs/hyper-util)  
``webpki-tokio`` | **no** | Uses a compiled-in set of root certificates trusted by Mozilla (via [``webpki-roots``](https://docs.rs/webpki-roots))  
``native-tokio`` | **yes** | Use the platform's native certificate store at runtime (via [``rustls-native-certs``](https://docs.rs/rustls-native-certs))  
``rustls-platform-verifier`` | **no** | Use the operating system's verifier for certificate verification (via [``rustls-platform-verifier``](https://docs.rs/rustls-platform-verifier))  
``ring`` | **no** | Enables use of the [``ring``](https://docs.rs/ring) backend for [``rustls``](https://docs.rs/rustls)  
``tls12`` | **yes** | Enables support for TLS 1.2 (only TLS 1.3 supported when disabled)  
``logging`` | **yes** | Enables logging of protocol-level diagnostics and errors via [``log``](https://docs.rs/log)  
``fips`` | **no** | Enables support for using a FIPS 140-3 compliant backend via AWS-LC (enables ``aws-lc-rs`` feature)

## [§](https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls/latest/hyper_rustls/#hyper-rustls)hyper-rustls
A pure-Rust HTTPS connector for [hyper](https://hyper.rs), based on [Rustls](https://github.com/rustls/rustls).
### [§](https://docs.rs/hyper-rustls/latest/hyper_rustls/#example-client)Example client
```
use http::StatusCode;
use http_body_util::Empty;
use hyper::body::Bytes;
use hyper_util::client::legacy::Client;
use hyper_util::rt::TokioExecutor;
let mut rt = tokio::runtime::Runtime::new().unwrap();
let url = ("https://hyper.rs").parse().unwrap();
let https = hyper_rustls::HttpsConnectorBuilder::new()
  .with_native_roots()
  .expect("no native root CA certificates found")
  .https_only()
  .enable_http1()
  .build();
let client: Client<_, Empty<Bytes>> = Client::builder(TokioExecutor::new()).build(https);
let res = rt.block_on(client.get(url)).unwrap();
assert_eq!(res.status(), StatusCode::OK);
```

enriched_crate.readme_summary: The `hyper-rustls` crate provides a pure-Rust HTTPS connector for the `hyper` HTTP library, leveraging the `rustls` TLS implementation for secure communication. It includes an `HttpsConnectorBuilder` for flexible configuration, support for HTTP/1, and native root CA certificates. Key features include customizable server name resolution, TLS stream handling, and integration with asynchronous runtimes like Tokio.
enriched_crate.factual_counterfactual:
### Pair 1: HTTPS Connector  
✅ Factual: The `hyper-rustls` crate provides an `HttpsConnector` that enables secure HTTPS connections for the `hyper` HTTP client, using Rustls as the TLS backend.  
❌ Counterfactual: The `hyper-rustls` crate supports HTTPS connections by default but relies on OpenSSL as its TLS backend instead of Rustls.  

---

### Pair 2: Root Certificate Management  
✅ Factual: The `HttpsConnectorBuilder` in `hyper-rustls` allows users to configure root certificates using native system roots or custom certificates for TLS validation.  
❌ Counterfactual: The `HttpsConnectorBuilder` in `hyper-rustls` does not support native system roots and requires users to manually specify all root certificates.  

---

### Pair 3: Server Name Resolution  
✅ Factual: The `hyper-rustls` crate includes the `DefaultServerNameResolver` and `FixedServerNameResolver` for resolving server names during TLS handshakes.  
❌ Counterfactual: The `hyper-rustls` crate does not provide any server name resolution functionality, requiring users to implement their own resolver logic.
